commit.message:
cmd/fmt: recognize tsv automatically

All commands except for `xsv fmt` recognized tsv files automatically,
and we seem to do this by surreptitiously using `(default: ,)` instead
of `[default: ,]` in our docopt description. The former does nothing,
while the latter actually specifies a default value. We want the former
so that our reader configuration knows when to try to be smart, which it
won't be if it's given an explicit delimiter.

Fixes #112

commit.message:
Numerical sorting now treats non-integer numbers as f64.

To fix an issue where xsv would not sort non-integers properly, this
commit makes xsv able to consider non-integers as f64. For integers, we
still compare using i64 v i64, while we treat any other number as f64
vs. f64 comparsion.
